commit.message: Update README.rst
set version to 1.20
setup: add long description

setup: fix pygments deps

Since 2.6.0, pygment do not support Python 2 so we need a check
on version to avoid a problem at install.
set version to 1.19
fix parallel execution

automatically include local directory

If there is a directory specified in the filename we automatically
add the directory the file is in as the include directory.

serialize with json instead of pickle

It should be safer.
fix linter warning and upgrade version
cosmetic fixes for linter
grep mode: fix multiline case
fix typo in comment

used: fix equality match

In the case where a = b and a is in the correct type, then we have
a match on the result of the equality so "a = b". This is true but
not sure this is what we want.
allow multiple match on the same line

fix grep mode display

Character before match was not displayed.
Update version to 1.17
set only color in grep mode for tty
color attribute in grep mode

add grep mode for color

Colorize only the match in the output.

Fix syntax error in python3 environment.

When I run coccigrep python3, I got following syntax error.

masami@saga:~$ coccigrep -v -t test_t test.c
Running: spatch --recursive-includes -sp_file /tmp/tmp0di5wo0y.cocci
test.c.
init_defs_builtins: /usr/lib/coccinelle/standard.h
HANDLING: test.c
  File "<string>", line 6
    print "%s:%s:%s:%s:%s" %
(p.file,p.line,p.column,p.line_end,p.column_end)
                         ^
SyntaxError: invalid syntax
while running simple python string:
from coccinelle import *
from coccilib.iteration import Iteration

for p in p1:
    print "%s:%s:%s:%s:%s" %
(p.file,p.line,p.column,p.line_end,p.column_end)
:
Failure in rule starting on line 19
Fatal error: exception Yes_pycocci.Pycocciexception
No match found in test.c

So, use print() style to support Python3.

setup: use and complete install_requires

This allows automatic installation of dependencies at install.
Update version to 1.16.

Add support for python 3.4

Coccigrep fails to run on python 3.4 with the following error:

  Traceback (most recent call last):
    File "/usr/bin/coccigrep", line 143, in <module>
      coccigrep.run(files)
    File "/usr/lib/python3.4/site-packages/coccigrep/coccigrep.py", line 489, in run
      if not ret.startswith('cexceptions\n'):
  TypeError: startswith first arg must be bytes or a tuple of bytes, not str

This can be fixed by explicit conversions to/from utf8.
Update version to 1.15.
Add python3 support
update version to 1.14.
document void option usage in vim plugin

have for result an invalid coccigrep command.
forcing a type to be present was arbitrary
